#Text=The San Antonio Spurs ( 7 - 2 ) defeated the Philadelphia 76ers ( 0 - 10 ) 92 - 83 on Saturday .
#Text=This was a mismatch on paper and that ended up being the case on Saturday .
#Text=The Spurs dominated in nearly every category , as they recorded more rebounds , assists , blocks and steals than the Sixers .
#Text=It was a relatively clean game played all - around though , as there were only 28 combined turnovers between both teams .
#Text=It was a much closer game than expected and the credit has to go to this winless Sixers team to put in a strong effort night - after - night despite losing every single game .
#Text=Luckily for Philadelphia , this will be the only time they 'll have to face the Spurs in San Antonio this season .
#Text=This was probably the best performance from the Sixers all year , despite in a losing effort .
#Text=They not only shot better than the Spurs , but nearly split the turnover battle ( 15 - 13 ) .
#Text=They were led once again by rookie Jahlil Okafor , who tallied 21 points and 12 rebounds in the loss .
#Text=They also got some nice contributions off the bench , as all five players off the bench had at least five points and two rebounds .
#Text=It 's a rough time in Philadelphia right now , but they have to look at performances like these as victories and take them with a grain of salt .
#Text=They 'll look to build off this loss when they host the Dallas Mavericks on Monday .
#Text=Coach Greg Popovich is probably not very happy with this performance , but he 'll take the win .
#Text=The Spurs came in as 16 - point favorites and never really seemed close to covering that spread .
#Text=San Antonio was led by LaMarcus Aldridge , who tallied 17 points and 19 rebounds in his best game in a Spurs uniform .
#Text=Tim Duncan recorded a season - high 15 points and blocked five shots as well in the victory .
#Text=He has now matched or scored more in every preceding game this season and that 's likely a case of the 39 - year - old getting his legs underneath him .
#Text=This is obviously a dangerous team and a disappointing win like this just shows how good they are .
#Text=The Spurs next game will be on Monday against the Portland Trail Blazers ,
